[DQC.US.0081.9277] The line item concept us-gaap:CostOfRevenue with a value of 21,314 is represented as a child of us-gaap:OperatingExpenses with a value of 301,269 in the companies extension taxonomy role 00000004 - Statement - CONDENSED STATEMENTS OF OPERATIONS (UNAUDITED). The element us-gaap:CostOfRevenue however, is not represented as a component of us-gaap:OperatingExpenses in the calculation relationships defined in the US GAAP taxonomy. The US-GAAP taxonomies include us-gaap:CostOfRevenue as a sibling element (or child of that sibling) relative to us-gaap:OperatingExpenses in the calculation relationships of the US GAAP taxonomy. Please review the element selection to determine that an appropriate element has been used for the parent element us-gaap:OperatingExpenses and the child element us-gaap:CostOfRevenue. The element CostOfRevenue includes those expenses which can be clearly related to production and included in cost of sales or services whereas these are excluded in Operating Expenses. Consider using the element CostsAndExpenses instead of using OperatingExpenses as the parent of CostOfRevenue. The element CostsAndExpenses includes operating expenses and CostOfRevenue.
The properties of this us-gaap:CostOfRevenue fact are:
Period :2022-02-01 to 2022-04-30 Dimensions : Unit : USD
Rule Element Id:9277 Rule version: 22.0.0RC1 - http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1190370/000173112223001281/e4854_10q.htm 1486
